   <mods:abstract>Although Dr. Watts has not yet been able to determine the nature of little
            Maria's complaint, he feels that she is much improved. He has given her nothing so far
            but "small doses of rhubarb, a little qusia [sic] and few tablespoonful of lime water to
            be taken during the day. He says this is preparatory to iron filings, the effect of
            which he hoped to render permanent by preparing her stomach to receive it." Augusta
            hopes that John Jay's rheumatism has not become more painful. "My dear Mother" suffered
            a painful attack of rheumatism, which has confined her to bed.</mods:abstract>
